Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} on to boil for the pasta. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Trim the @courgette{1}. Use a #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the courgette, stopping at the spongy centre. Zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}.

Once boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. When ready, reserve some of the pasta water (see pantry for amount), then drain in a #colander{}.

Pop the pasta back into the pan, drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the courgette ribbons and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}, then stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time and cook until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Once cooked, transfer everything to a large #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Put your (now empty) frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{} (if needed). Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Turn occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the shallot to the chicken pan and cook, stirring occasionally, until the shallot has softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @reserved pasta water{100%ml}, then simmer until reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Mix in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and heat through until piping hot, then season with @pepper{}. Stir through three quarters of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir the cooked pasta through your sauce along with half the greens. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick. Add a pinch of lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and add more lemon juice, salt and pepper if needed.

Share the creamy chicken pasta between your bowls and top with the remaining greens. Finish with a sprinkle of the remaining hard Italian style cheese. Enjoy!